A ledger.



A fund.



A circle.



A promise.



A return.



The past has already given us evidence.



The future is waiting for our version.



So gather the ten.



Write the purpose.



Collect the dues.



Keep the record.



Build the first container.



Finish the first 100 days.



Then do it again.



And again.



Until the circle becomes an institution.



Until the institution supports businesses.



Until the businesses help acquire property.



Until the property anchors wealth.



Until the wealth protects the community.



Until political power grows from organized life.



Until children inherit not only stories of what was lost, but systems for what can be built.



That is the work.



That is the blueprint.



That is what comes before the next Black Wall Street.
